HEADWORD: Frondation
<hw>Fron*da"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>frondatio</ets>, from <ets>frons</ets>. See <er>Frond</er>.]</ety>
<def>The act of stripping, as trees, of leaves or branches; a kind of
pruning.</def> <rj><au>Evelyn.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

